Feature Request:

For now, when posting in slack channel message with the huge amount of messages, Jira cloud is expanded them all, and there is a too long message appeared (feature "Have @jirabot automatically show previews of Jira issues when issue keys or URLs are mentioned in your channel" is turned ON && Message style is chosen "Clean").

For example, if some manager composes the summary of problems to verify they usually post the list of related issue links. For several items, it is OK to expand details, but for the list of 20, they got a message of crazy sizes from Jira Cloud Bot.

So I don't know how to better handle that:
1) maybe give an option for "expand only non-links (texted Jira issues number)". JIRA-123 is expanded, 
2) or provide an option for "Expand items count limit". Example: 
{code}
messagesCountLimit = 5
jiraTicketsInUserMessageCount (founded count of JIRA ticket numbers in the message)

if (jiraTicketsInUserMessageCount less then or equal `messageLimit`) {
  expand them as usual
} else {
  do not expand them at all 
}
{code}

